US Consumer Price Index and Inflation (CPI):
This dataset provides a historical view of the Consumer Price Index for All Urban Consumers (CPI-U) in the United States, which is a key measure of inflation. The data allows for tracking changes in purchasing power 
and inflation trends over time.

The link provided below can be used to access dataset:

https://datahub.io/core/cpi-us

How to Download the CPI Dataset:
Under the "Data Previews" section, select your preferred file format (CSV, JSON) to download the dataset directly.

Dataset Details:
Frequency: Monthly data, providing granular insights into inflation trends.

Variables:
Date: The time period (month and year) of the data.
CPI Value: The Consumer Price Index value, available in both seasonally adjusted and unadjusted formats.
Source: The dataset originates from the United States Bureau of Labor Statistics (BLS), ensuring credibility and reliability.
Period Covered: Includes historical data spanning multiple decades, enabling comprehensive analysis of long-term inflation trends.
